replies.body:
Wrong facts are strong with this one. 
1 The deep web is completely normal and not really dangerous. Wanna go into the deep web? Go access your profile on avicus and click on edit. Boom. Wasn't hard right? Deep web are just sites that aren't listed on Google and that mostly aren't accessible as a guest (like if you're not logged into avicus you obviously can't edit your profile). The dark web is part of the deep web tho but obviously you won't come across it easily. 

2. The deep web was made for the sole purpose that you can be anonymous. It uses multiple encryption proxys and layers called onion. The Tor browser also stands for The onion router for that reason. Obviously you're not untraceable but it's a huge effort to do so
